element.name: Sidetracked - Portmarnock by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: Portmarnock railway station is located on the Dublin-Belfast Railway line

long-description.p:
The station opened in 1844 it consists of the main building
built by Great Northern Railway it only had wooden waiting rooms on either side untill the DART service was extended from Howth Junction in 2000.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.
